  <h1 id="maincontent">PSA Audio scripts</h1>
  <p>Looking for a creative way to share information and promote PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention and the events and activities designed to create safe schools and communities? These free audio scripts are designed to use during school announcements, radio air time or can even be adapted for use on social media!</p>

  <h2><strong>PACER's National Bullying Prevention Center &ndash; PSAs</strong></h2>
  <p><strong>15 seconds</strong>&nbsp;</p>
  <ul>
    <li><p>PACER's National Bullying Prevention Center is taking action against bullying  and you can, too. To learn how, visit PACER.org/Bullying. Remember, the End of  Bullying Begins With You! PACER.org/bullying.</p></li>
    <li><p>Want to do something about bullying? PACER's National Bullying Prevention Center  offers the tools you need. Find free resources, classroom toolkits, and  websites for children and teens at PACER.org/Bullying. That&rsquo;s  PACER.org/Bullying.</p></li>
</ul>
  
  <p><strong>30 seconds</strong></p>
  <ul>
  	<li><p>No one should fear being bullied at school or online. PACER&rsquo;s  National Bullying Prevention Center has free resources  for children and teens. Show kids you care!&nbsp; Tell them about  KidsAgainstBullying.org and TeensAgainstBullying.org, websites created just for  them. And learn what you can do at PACER.org/Bullying. The End of Bullying  Begins With You!&nbsp; Visit PACER.org/bullying  today.</p></li>
  	  <li><p>Did you know that one of every four students will be bullied this year? Chances are this is happening to someone you know and care about. Now is the time to change what has happened to so many for too long. The End of Bullying Begins With You, now is the time to join the cause.  Visit PACER.org/bullying today.</p>
  	</li>
  </ul>


  <h2>National Bullying Prevention Month<strong> &ndash; </strong>PSAs</h2>
  <p><strong>15 seconds</strong></p>
  <ul>
      <li><p>October is National Bullying Prevention Month, a time to take action against bullying. Join PACER's National Bullying Prevention Center and show kids you care. Get involved at PACER.org/bullying. The End of Bullying Begins With You!</p></li>
        <li><p>October is National Bullying Prevention Month, a great time to take action against bullying. Free resources from PACER's National Bullying Prevention Center make it easy to get involved! Learn how at PACER.org/Bullying.</p>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>30 seconds</strong></p>
  <ul>
  	<li><p>More than 13 million children in America will be bullied this year, and the results can be tragic. October is National Bullying Prevention Month, which was created by the Minneapolis-based PACER Center. You can show that you care by wearing orange on for Unity Day, or by getting involved in bullying prevention activities in your community. To learn more about PACER&rsquo;s helpful resources &ndash; or to support the cause &ndash; visit PACER.org/bullying. And remember, the end of bullying begins with you!</p>
    </li></ul>
     <h2>Unity Day</h2>
    <p><strong>15 seconds</strong></p>
     <ul>
     <li><p>October 19th is Unity Day, a day to wear orange and unite against bullying. Make it Orange and Make it End! Join PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center, learn more at PACER.org/bullying.</p></li>
     </ul>
     <p><strong>30 seconds</strong></p>
     <ul>
     <li><p>Unity Day! Make it ORANGE and make it end! What are your true colors when it comes to bullying? If you care about safe and supportive schools and communities make your color ORANGE on Unity Day. That&rsquo;s the day everyone can come together&mdash;in schools, communities, and online &mdash; and send one large ORANGE message of support, hope, and unity to show that we are united against bullying and united for kindness, acceptance and inclusion. Learn more at PACER.org/Bullying</p>
     </li>
     </ul>
       	  <h2>Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying</h2>
  <p><strong>30 seconds</strong></p>
  	   <ul>
       <li><p>More than 13 million children in America will be bullied this year, and the results can be tragic. October is PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Month, and you can show your support by participating in PACER&rsquo;s Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying in Bloomington. All proceeds raised from this fun, family event will help Minnesota children be safe. Register today &ndash; or pledge your support &ndash; by visiting PACER.org/bullying. And remember, the end of bullying begins with you!</p></li>
       </ul>

       
  
  
  
